This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for language identification, which are typically covered under the arXiv category of Computer Science - Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of feed-forward networks and decoders, which are common techniques in deep learning and neural networks, falling under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image-based language identification, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions the use of optimization techniques for improving the performance of the model, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
